\mathcal{H} = \lbrace u\in \mathbb{R}^n \mid \langle x, (1, 1, ...., 1) \rangle = 0 \rbrace 
\frac{1}{n}\sum\limits_{i=1}^n x_i = 0
c,d \in \mathcal{H} 
e_c, e_d \in \mathbb{R}
\left \Vert c \right \Vert > e_c 
\left \Vert d \right \Vert > e_d 
 x,y \in \mathcal{H} 
\left \Vert x-c \right \Vert < e_c 
\left \Vert y-d \right \Vert < e_d 
x
y
\frac{\langle x, y\rangle}{\left \Vert x \right \Vert \left \Vert y \right \Vert } 
